# Agent instructions

**Read `README.md` first** for local setup, services, integrations, and reference docs.
If docs and code disagree, trust code and update docs in the same change.
If anything is unclear or instructions conflict, STOP and ask.

## Global rules

Cursor environment does not always automatically include my global user rules
in your context (it is a known bug), especially in cloud environments. If you did not
get those global user rules always included, read the frontmatter of all rule files
in `~/.cursor/rules` and read in full those that are relevant to your context.

Before starting, you must read the relevant global user rules in `~/.cursor/rules/`.
All rule files have frontmatter with information about when it is relevant.

## Code and verification

After you finish, run `pnpm fix` and `pnpm check` (and `pnpm build` when relevant).
Write simple, minimal code.
Prefer existing patterns.
Good accessibility is required.
Do not add unrequested features or APIs.
Store temporary artifacts in `tmp/`, not the repo root.

If `pnpm check` misses `$env/static/*` exports, run `pnpm sync`.

## Design and brand

On UI or visual work, read `BRAND.md` first for the why, then `DESIGN.md` for the how.
Ship visual changes together with the matching `DESIGN.md` update.

Use the `brand-md` and `design-md` skills when creating or maintaining these files.

## Git hooks

`lefthook` runs `pnpm check`, `pnpm lint`, and `pnpm format` on `git push`.
Install hooks via `pnpm install` (the `prepare` script runs `lefthook install`).

## Languages

English-only. User-facing copy in `src/` is English. Source code, doc files, AI chat,
commits, PRs, and issues stay in English.
